Alex wrote:

&gt; Now I have another issue, on the recovery of a job using a checkpoint, I
&gt; need to run some database calls to clean up objects stored, and change
&gt; references.  What would be the best approach to do this after the
&gt; restoration has run, but prior to running the job.

The CrawlStatusListener#crawlStarted looks to run early enough -- it 
happens before the crawl actual gets going.  But in previous message I 
talked of it being a little awkward getting your CrawlStatusListener 
implementation into place early enough.  Easiest might be your own 
CrawlJobHandler afterall.  And if it turns out that crawlStarted is not 
early enough, if you have your own CJH, you can run your processing 
before new crawl job is set up in CJH#startNextJob or 
CJH#startNextJobInternal.
St.Ack

